The inverted pendulum system consists of a cart of mass (M) that moves horizontally and a rigid pendulum of mass (m) and length (l) in m pivoted on the cart, as shown in Figure 2. The state variables are the cart position (x) in m, cart velocity (
x ˙
) in m/s, pendulum angle (θ) in rad measured from the upright equilibrium, and angular velocity (
θ ˙
) in rad/s. The control input is the horizontal force (F) in N applied to the cart.
